\begin_layout Subsection*
The Sandbox Setup
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Scala is a moving target.
 Because it is so actively researched,
 the environment around it evolves quickly.
 Usually,
 this leads to a "setup tax"—
an hour of fighting environment variables before you write a single line of code.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We’re going to skip that.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Instead of installing Scala across your entire Operating System,
 we’re going to build a 
\series bold
Portable Sandbox
\series default
.
 This keeps your project self-contained and your system clean.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
You only need two things to get started.
 Create a folder for this book (let’s call it 
\emph on
scala-sandbox
\emph default
) and follow these steps:
\end_layout

